==Danish==

===Etymology===
From {{der|da|gml|be-}}, from {{der|da|osx|bi-}}, from {{der|da|gem-pro|*bi-}}.

===Prefix===
{{da-prefix}}

# Forms adjectives from nouns, with the sense "having noun".
#: ''{{l|da|hår}}'' ("hair") &rarr; ''{{l|da|behåret}}'' ("hairy")
#: ''{{l|da|hjerte}}'' ("heart") &rarr; ''{{l|da|behjertet}}'' ("hearty, brave")
# Forms verbs from adjectives, with the sense "making" (adjective); {{l|en|-ify}}.
#: ''{{l|da|svanger}}'' ("pregnant") &rarr; ''{{l|da|besvangre}}'' ("impregnate")
#: ''{{l|da|rolig}}'' ("calm") &rarr; ''{{l|da|berolige}}'' ("calm, soothe")
# Prepends to verbs, having no effect save making the verb transitive
#: ''{{l|da|tvivle}}'' &rarr; ''{{l|da|betvivle}}'' ("doubt")
#: ''{{l|da|kæmpe}}'' &rarr; ''{{l|da|bekæmpe}}'' ("fight")

====Usage notes====
Verbs formed with ''be-'' are transitive. Many such words are formed after {{l|en|Middle Low German}} words.

